							<overview>
<eaover>Facilities
a.Large scale operation that services various public and private customers in the transfer of various cargoes.
b.Only successful geocoding is included in a dataset and reported in the attributes latitude, longitude, and geosource.</eaover>
								<eadetcit>Directionality is directly related to the facility table, includes cargo or commodity records that have mode 1 to mode 2 restrictions or limitations requiring it to flow in only one direction.</eadetcit>
								<eadetcit>Cargo is directly related to the facility table, used aggregated classifications of cargo types and commodity specific cargo types.</eadetcit>
								<eadetcit>Commodity is directly related to the facility table, includes classifications based on the Commodity Flow Survey (USDOT/RITA/BTS) categorizations.</eadetcit>
							</overview>
